description: From Old French raisine, rousine, variants of r√©sine. See resin.

entries.meaning: (organic chemistry) A solid form of resin, obtained from liquid resin by vaporizing its volatile components.

verbs.description: rosin (third-person singular simple present rosins, present participle rosining, simple past and past participle rosined)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To apply rosin to (something); to rub or cover with rosin.
examples: We waited expectantly as the guest violinist rosined his bow in preparation for playing.
